---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import Header from '../components/Header.astro';
import Footer from '../components/Footer.astro';

const title = 'Privacy Policy | Nubo Baby Tracker';
const description = 'Nubo is privacy-first. Your baby\'s data stays on your phone, not our servers. No account required. No data sold. Read our full privacy policy.';

const jsonLd = {
  "@context": "https://schema.org",
  "@type": "WebPage",
  "name": "Privacy Policy",
  "description": description,
  "url": "https://www.nubotracker.com/privacy-policy/",
  "publisher": {
    "@type": "Organization",
    "name": "Clicksie LLC",
    "url": "https://www.nubotracker.com"
  }
};
---

<BaseLayout title={title} description={description} jsonLd={jsonLd}>
  <Header />
  <main>
    <section class="page-hero">
      <div class="container">
        <p class="overline">Privacy by Design</p>
        <h1>Privacy Policy</h1>
        <p class="page-hero-sub">
          Nubo is built by parents, for parents. Your baby's data is yours, not ours.
          Here's exactly how we handle it.
        </p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="policy-content">
      <div class="container policy-inner">
        <p class="policy-updated">Last updated: March 30, 2026</p>

        <div class="policy-summary">
          <h2>The short version</h2>
          <ul class="summary-list">
            <li>No account is required to use the Nubo device or app</li>
            <li>Activity data (feedings, sleep, diapers) is stored locally on your phone</li>
            <li>We do not have access to your baby's tracking data</li>
            <li>Caregiver sharing uses end-to-end encryption</li>
            <li>Backups go to your own iCloud or Google Drive, not our servers</li>
            <li>We never sell, rent, or share your personal information</li>
            <li>No third-party advertising or tracking SDKs in the app</li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <article class="policy-body">
          <h2>1. What data does the Nubo device collect?</h2>
          <p>
            The Nubo device records button presses (feeding, sleep, diaper events) with timestamps.
            This data is stored on the device until it syncs to the Nubo companion app via Bluetooth.
            The device does not connect to the internet and does not transmit data to any server.
          </p>

          <h2>2. What data does the Nubo app collect?</h2>
          <p>
            The Nubo app stores your baby's activity logs locally on your phone. If you choose to
            create an optional account for caregiver sharing, we store only the minimum information
            needed to enable collaboration:
          </p>
          <ul>
            <li>Email address (for account identification)</li>
            <li>Display name (shown to other caregivers)</li>
            <li>Encrypted activity data (shared between linked caregivers)</li>
          </ul>
          <p>
            We do not collect your location, contacts, photos, or any other personal data beyond
            what is listed above.
          </p>

          <h2>3. Where is data stored?</h2>
          <p>
            Activity data is stored locally on your device by default. If you enable caregiver
            sharing, encrypted data is temporarily relayed through our servers to sync between
            devices. We cannot read this data because it is end-to-end encrypted.
          </p>
          <p>
            Optional backups are stored in your personal iCloud or Google Drive account, not on
            Nubo servers.
          </p>

          <h2>4. Caregiver sharing and encryption</h2>
          <p>
            When you invite a caregiver, a secure sharing link is generated. Activity data shared
            between caregivers is encrypted end-to-end. Nubo servers act only as a relay and
            cannot decrypt or access the content of shared data.
          </p>

          <h2>5. Analytics and tracking</h2>
          <p>
            The Nubo app does not include third-party advertising SDKs. We may collect anonymous,
            aggregated usage statistics (such as which features are used most often) to improve
            the app experience. These statistics cannot be linked to individual users or babies.
          </p>
          <p>
            This website uses Plausible Analytics, a privacy-friendly analytics tool that does
            not use cookies and does not collect personal data.
          </p>

          <h2>6. Data retention and deletion</h2>
          <p>
            You can delete all your data at any time from within the Nubo app. If you delete your
            account, all associated data is permanently removed from our systems within 30 days.
            Local data on your phone can be removed by deleting the app.
          </p>

          <h2>7. Children's privacy</h2>
          <p>
            Nubo is a tool for parents and caregivers. We do not knowingly collect personal
            information from children. The app is intended for use by adults to track their
            baby's activities.
          </p>

          <h2>8. Third-party services</h2>
          <p>
            Nubo integrates with the following third-party services only when you choose to use them:
          </p>
          <ul>
            <li><strong>Apple iCloud / Google Drive</strong> for optional backup</li>
            <li><strong>Apple HealthKit</strong> for optional feeding data export (iOS only)</li>
          </ul>
          <p>
            Each of these services is governed by its own privacy policy. Nubo does not share your
            data with any other third parties.
          </p>

          <h2>9. Changes to this policy</h2>
          <p>
            We may update this privacy policy from time to time. Significant changes will be
            communicated through the app or on this page. The "Last updated" date at the top
            reflects the most recent revision.
          </p>

          <h2>10. Contact</h2>
          <p>
            If you have questions about this privacy policy or how Nubo handles your data,
            please reach out at
            <a href="mailto:support@clicksie.io">support@clicksie.io</a>.
          </p>

          <div class="policy-company">
            <p>
              <strong>Clicksie LLC</strong><br />
              Nubo Baby Tracker<br />
              <a href="https://www.nubotracker.com">www.nubotracker.com</a>
            </p>
          </div>
        </article>
      </div>
    </section>
  </main>
  <Footer />
</BaseLayout>


<style>
  .policy-content {
    padding: 4rem 0 6rem;
  }

  .policy-inner {
    max-width: 720px;
    margin: 0 auto;
  }

  .policy-updated {
    font-size: 0.8125rem;
    color: #999;
    margin-bottom: 2.5rem;
  }

  .policy-summary {
    background: var(--color-bg-soft);
    border-radius: var(--radius-xl);
    padding: 2.5rem;
    margin-bottom: 3rem;
  }

  .policy-summary h2 {
    font-size: 1.25rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    color: var(--color-text);
    margin-bottom: 1.25rem;
    letter-spacing: -0.02em;
  }

  .summary-list {
    list-style: none;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 0.6rem;
  }

  .summary-list li {
    font-size: 0.9375rem;
    color: #444;
    padding-left: 2rem;
    position: relative;
    line-height: 1.5;
  }

  .summary-list li::before {
    content: '✓';
    position: absolute;
    left: 0;
    color: var(--color-brand);
    font-weight: 700;
  }

  .policy-body h2 {
    font-size: 1.25rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    color: var(--color-text);
    margin-top: 2.5rem;
    margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
    letter-spacing: -0.02em;
  }

  .policy-body p {
    font-size: 0.9375rem;
    color: #444;
    line-height: 1.8;
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
  }

  .policy-body ul {
    list-style: none;
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 0.4rem;
  }

  .policy-body ul li {
    font-size: 0.9375rem;
    color: #444;
    padding-left: 1.5rem;
    position: relative;
    line-height: 1.7;
  }

  .policy-body ul li::before {
    content: '·';
    position: absolute;
    left: 0;
    color: var(--color-brand);
    font-weight: 900;
    font-size: 1.25rem;
    line-height: 1;
    top: 4px;
  }

  .policy-body a {
    color: var(--color-brand);
    font-weight: 600;
    transition: color 0.2s;
  }

  .policy-body a:hover {
    color: var(--color-brand-dark);
  }

  .policy-company {
    margin-top: 3rem;
    padding-top: 2rem;
    border-top: 1px solid #eee;
    font-size: 0.875rem;
    color: var(--color-text-secondary);
    line-height: 1.7;
  }

  .policy-company a {
    color: var(--color-brand);
    font-weight: 600;
  }

  @media (max-width: 768px) {
    .page-hero { padding: 8rem 0 3rem; }
    .policy-summary { padding: 1.75rem; }
  }
</style>
